   {
      "body" : "I'm starting to realize that @luke-jr's idea to accept 0-2 isn't such a bad idea after all. Just rename the argument  'verbosityLevel'. It is easier to use and understand from a user perspective than two booleans (we regularly get confused there in the tests ourselves). Also it'd remove having to deal with the redundant and nonsensical combo `verbose=false extraVerbose=true`. \r\n\r\nIt should still accept `false` and `true` too. For consistency we should do the same in `getrawtransaction`. This method currently accepts a `verbose` argument that can be `0` or `1` but not `false` or `true`. The mapping `false:0,true:1` should be added there (not in this pull though).\r\n\r\nAlso: needs rebase.\r\n",
      "created_at" : "2016-10-26T11:33:56Z",
